classes.documentation: This application holds a complete list of the source record keys for the transactions held in the DX.TRANSACTION file. DXCOYYDDDnnnnn is the key to a DX.CLOSEOUT record holding the details of the particular closeout. DXTRAYYDDDnnnnn is the key to a DX.TRADE record holding the details of all side of the trade. DXEOEYYDDDnnnnn where nnnnn is DX.EXCHANGE.MASTER(& end of exchange) key of the end of exchange processing that was run on YYDDD. Validation Rules None
classes.name: DX_TRANS_KEYS

properties.documentation: Key of the source record to which these transactions belong.
properties.name: DX_TRANS_KEYS

properties.documentation: Keys to the DX.TRANSACTION records which correspond to the source record.
properties.name: TRANSACTION_ID
en
properties.value: Indicates the User who Authorises the record

properties.name: en
properties.value: Date and time when record was audited

classes.documentation: This table can be used to track the status of records held in DX tables. It allows for a finer granularity of status than the standard T24 statuses because any status defined in DX.ITEM.STATUS.TYPE can be used. A record contains the current item status and records the statuses that the item has been in.

properties.documentation: The current status. A valid DX.ITEM.STATUS.TYPE.

properties.documentation: The date that the current status was set.
properties.name: CURR_DATE

properties.documentation: The time that the current status was set.

properties.documentation: A Multi-valued historical list of times at which an item status was set.

classes.documentation: This application allows the user to setup a default counterparty for a trade based on the contract class of the product being traded.For example,OTC FX trades are mostly traded between the customer and the banks own book therefore the use could set the module up to default the banks own book portfolio as the default counterparty for all OTC FX deals.
classes.name: DX_DEFAULT_CPARTY
